Cal27: NSD2.KO vs NSD1.KO

We find more upregulated genes in NSD2.KO than downregulated ones. However, both upregulated and downregulated genes are enriched in cellular structure development, although downregulated genes are also enriched in pathways in cancer.

Cal27: comparison of NSD knockouts

NSD.DKO has few DEGs when compared to NSD1.KO. Largest number of DEGs found between TKO and NSD2.KO. There appears to have some enriched pathways in TKO and in NSD2.KO compared to others, but few in NSD1.KO and none in NSD.DKO

DEG cutoff was FDR < 0.05 & |log2FC| > 2

Cal27: K36M-OE vs NSD1/2KO

Many more downregulated genes in NSD1KO compared to K36M-OE whereas NSD2.KO vs K36M-OE results in roughly equal DEGs in either direction.
